{"ts": "2026-06-12T17:42:42.000Z", "event": "planner", "msg": "Level X task analysis", "agent": "orchestrator-lx", "tokens_in": 965, "tokens_out": 1183, "elapsed_ms": 13307, "model": "deepseek-v4-pro", "prompt": "You are the Level X Orchestrator — the central intelligence of the system.\nYou plan, test, and report. You decide when to delegate to workers.\n\n## Task Analysis\nAnalyze the user's task and output a JSON plan:\n\n{\n  \"plan\": [\n    {\n      \"task_id\": \"short-name\",\n      \"description\": \"What this worker must produce\",\n      \"need_worker\": true\n    }\n  ],\n  \"key_requirements\": [\"list the 2-4 critical things that must work\"]\n}\n\n## Rules\n- Prefer ONE worker that handles EVERYTHING end-to-end. Only split if tasks\n  require fundamentally different expertise (e.g., Python backend + React frontend).\n- Most frontend UI tasks need exactly ONE worker: it writes HTML, CSS, and JS itself.\n- task_id must be unique short names like \"ui\", \"api\", \"docs\".\n- Each description must include exact output file names.\n- Output ONLY the JSON object — no markdown fences, no extra text.\n\n## User Request\nBuild a ChatGPT-style dashboard for running agent tasks. Files: index.html, styles.css, app.js.\n\nNON-NEGOTIABLE requirements (do these FIRST):\n1. Level dropdown: <select id=\"level\"> with options: levelx (default), baseline1, baseline2, level1b, 1, 2, 3\n2. Specialty dropdown: <select id=\"specialty\"> with options: frontend (default), backend, brand, fullstack, research\n3. REAL API calls: POST to http://localhost:8000/api/v1/run with {level, specialty, task, user}. Parse SSE stream with ReadableStream reader. NO mock data, NO setInterval, NO fake events.\n\nLayout:\n- Left sidebar 260px: history list + New Chat button. Scrollable internally.\n- Main area: chat messages (scrollable), fixed input bar at bottom\n- Top bar: username display + Logout\n- Full viewport, body overflow:hidden. Only sidebar and chat panel scroll.\n\nLogin: username input only. Save to localStorage(\"orcheeos_user\"). Skip if already saved.\n\nInput bar: text input + level dropdown + specialty dropdown + Run button. Send on Enter.\n\nSSE parsing (use exactly this pattern):\n```js\nconst res = await fetch(\"/api/v1/run\", {\n  method:\"POST\", headers:{\"Content-Type\":\"application/json\"},\n  body:JSON.stringify({level:level.value, specialty:spec.value, task:input.value, user:username})\n});\nconst reader = res.body.getReader();\nconst decoder = new TextDecoder();\nlet buf = \"\";\nwhile(true) {\n  const {done, value} = await reader.read();\n  if(done) break;\n  buf += decoder.decode(value, {stream:true});\n  const lines = buf.split(\"\\n\");\n  buf = lines.pop();\n  for(const line of lines) {\n    if(line.startsWith(\"data: \")) {\n      const evt = JSON.parse(line.slice(6));\n      if(!taskId && evt.task_id) taskId = evt.task_id;\n      addLogBubble(evt);\n      if(evt.event===\"task_complete\"||evt.event===\"run_finished\") showActions(taskId);\n    }\n  }\n}\n```\n\nLog display: each SSE event as a left-aligned bubble with colored pill badge (planner=blue, worker=green, error=red, llm_call=purple, tool_call=gray, report=yellow) + message text + token/model info.\n\nAfter task_complete/run_finished: show Preview button -> window.open(\"/api/v1/preview/frontend/\"+username+\"/\"+taskId+\"/main/index.html\") and Download ZIP -> window.open(\"/api/v1/artifacts/\"+taskId).\n\nHistory: localStorage key \"orcheeos_history\" as JSON array of {taskId, preview, timestamp, level, specialty}. Store events array. Click to reload.\n\nHealth: fetch /api/v1/health on load, show \"Server Offline\" banner if not ok. Check every 30s.\n\nDark theme, clean typography, monospace for logs.", "meta": {}}
{"ts": "2026-06-12T17:43:00.000Z", "event": "agent_creator", "msg": "Level X Agent Creator — generating workers", "agent": "agent-creator-lx", "tokens_in": 1122, "tokens_out": 1965, "elapsed_ms": 17958, "model": "deepseek-v4-pro", "prompt": "You are the Level X Agent Creator. Create worker configurations with tool suggestions.\n\n## Available Tools (full menu)\n[\"read_file\", \"write_file\", \"list_files\", \"run_command\", \"render_html_screenshot\", \"render_html_file_screenshot\", \"validate_html\", \"validate_css\", \"read_image\", \"generate_image\"]\n\n## Recommended Tools (suggest these for every worker)\nwrite_file, read_file, list_files, generate_image, render_html_file_screenshot, read_image, validate_html, validate_css, run_command\n\n## Task Plan\n[\n  {\n    \"task_id\": \"ui\",\n    \"description\": \"Build the complete ChatGPT-style dashboard as specified. Create three files: index.html, styles.css, app.js. Implement the full viewport layout with a 260px left sidebar (history list + New Chat button, internally scrollable) and a main area (scrollable chat messages, fixed bottom input bar). The top bar must show username and Logout button. Login requires only username, stored in localStorage as 'orcheeos_user', and skipped if already present. The input bar must include a text input, a level dropdown (id='level' with options: levelx, baseline1, baseline2, level1b, 1, 2, 3; default levelx), a specialty dropdown (id='specialty' with options: frontend, backend, brand, fullstack, research; default frontend), and a Run button. Sending on Enter must be supported. All API calls must be real: POST to http://localhost:8000/api/v1/run with JSON body {level, specialty, task, user}; parse the SSE stream exactly as shown using ReadableStream reader, decoder, and line buffering. Display each SSE event as a left-aligned bubble with a colored pill badge (planner=blue, worker=green, error=red, llm_call=purple, tool_call=gray, report=yellow) plus message text and token/model info. After 'task_complete' or 'run_finished', show Preview and Download ZIP buttons that open correct URLs. Store history in localStorage key 'orcheeos_history' as JSON array of {taskId, preview, timestamp, level, specialty, events}; clicking a history item reloads its events. Implement a health check on load (fetch /api/v1/health) and every 30 seconds, showing a 'Server Offline' banner if not ok. Use a dark theme, clean typography, and monospace fonts for logs. Body overflow must be hidden; only the sidebar and chat panel scroll.\",\n    \"need_worker\": true\n  }\n]\n\n## Rules\n- Create EXACTLY the workers specified in the plan — no extra, no missing\n- Each worker gets the RECOMMENDED tools above PLUS any additional tools from the full menu that are needed\n- Each worker's system_prompt MUST push them toward COMPLETE end-to-end delivery:\n  \"You are responsible for the COMPLETE deliverable. Solve everything end-to-end. Write ALL files. Validate ALL output. If you need an image, use generate_image. If you need to verify, use screenshots. Do NOT leave work for others.\"\n- worker_name MUST match the task_id from the plan\n- system_prompt: detailed role + boundaries + workflow + output format\n- Keep it simple: 1-2 workers is ideal\n- Output ONLY valid JSON — no markdown fences\n\n## Output Format\n{\n  \"workers\": [\n    {\n      \"worker_name\": \"task_id_from_plan\",\n      \"system_prompt\": \"Full custom system instructions pushing toward end-to-end completion\",\n      \"tool_names\": [\"tool1\", \"tool2\", \"...\"]\n    }\n  ]\n}\n\n## Reference Templates (suggestions only - pick what makes sense)\n[\n  {\n    \"name\": \"ux\",\n    \"tools\": [\n      \"read_file\",\n      \"write_file\",\n      \"list_files\",\n      \"generate_image\"\n    ]\n  },\n  {\n    \"name\": \"html\",\n    \"tools\": [\n      \"read_file\",\n      \"write_file\",\n      \"list_files\",\n      \"validate_html\",\n      \"render_html_file_screenshot\",\n      \"generate_image\",\n      \"run_command\"\n    ]\n  },\n  {\n    \"name\": \"css\",\n    \"tools\": [\n      \"read_file\",\n      \"write_file\",\n      \"list_files\",\n      \"validate_css\",\n      \"run_command\"\n    ]\n  },\n  {\n    \"name\": \"js\",\n    \"tools\": [\n      \"read_file\",\n      \"write_file\",\n      \"list_files\",\n      \"run_command\"\n    ]\n  },\n  {\n    \"name\": \"tester\",\n    \"tools\": [\n      \"read_file\",\n      \"write_file\",\n      \"list_files\",\n      \"validate_html\",\n      \"validate_css\",\n      \"render_html_file_screenshot\",\n      \"read_image\",\n      \"run_command\"\n    ]\n  }\n]", "meta": {}}
